WEBVTT

00:00.783 --> 00:03.525
[Camille] So, my mapmaker,
take me away from here?

00:03.612 --> 00:05.179
[Pascal]
Where do you want to go?

00:05.309 --> 00:06.963
[Camille] Somewhere
we can always be together.

00:07.094 --> 00:08.530
[Pascal]
Marry me, Camille.

00:08.660 --> 00:10.836
You can't afford me, Pascal.

00:10.967 --> 00:12.795
[Pascal] My father's title,
his fortune,

00:12.925 --> 00:14.188
should have been mine
when he died,

00:14.275 --> 00:15.580
but you poisoned him
against me.

00:15.711 --> 00:17.539
It's not my fault
he fell in love with me.

00:17.626 --> 00:19.193
I will not spend
the night with you.

00:19.280 --> 00:20.977
You will stay.
I've paid for you.

00:21.108 --> 00:23.675
[dramatic music plays]

00:23.806 --> 00:26.287
-Who is she?
-Geneviève de Merteuil.

00:26.417 --> 00:28.202
Tell me I am your only lover.

00:28.332 --> 00:30.073
She's married.

00:30.160 --> 00:33.163
She will do or pay anything
to save her reputation.

00:33.294 --> 00:35.035
The Marquis
has left Saint-Domingue.

00:35.165 --> 00:37.428
He will return
before the month is out.

00:37.515 --> 00:39.822
There are more letters,
all from other women.

00:39.952 --> 00:41.737
All write of love.

00:41.824 --> 00:43.608
[Geneviève]
What do you want from me?

00:43.739 --> 00:46.307
Teach me, and I will give you
back every one of your letters.

00:46.437 --> 00:48.613
Privilege cannot be learned.

00:48.700 --> 00:50.659
I have been
in a great house before.

00:50.789 --> 00:53.140
I have only to send one letter
to your husband.

00:53.227 --> 00:54.663
If you have it.

00:56.186 --> 00:58.884
Welcome to the opera, Camille.

00:59.059 --> 01:02.018
♪ ♪

01:02.149 --> 01:05.152
[hoofbeats clopping]

01:13.595 --> 01:17.077
Your freedom, Madame,
as you have given me mine.

01:23.605 --> 01:24.997
Your letters.

01:27.957 --> 01:30.916
We should never be
at the mercy of men again.

01:31.003 --> 01:32.875
I have taken off my armor.

01:34.920 --> 01:38.054
There's nothing left
to protect...

01:38.185 --> 01:40.578
except perhaps you.

01:40.709 --> 01:43.625
[dramatic music plays]

01:43.755 --> 01:45.888
You are my guest, Camille.

01:48.064 --> 01:50.893
This house is your house,

01:51.023 --> 01:53.461
your opportunity.

01:53.591 --> 01:56.812
Use it...

01:56.942 --> 01:59.815
and you will flourish in Paris.

01:59.989 --> 02:02.731
♪ ♪

02:05.777 --> 02:08.389
There is power...

02:08.519 --> 02:12.044
in other people's secrets.

02:12.175 --> 02:14.656
They will do anything
to keep them hidden.

02:14.786 --> 02:17.441
Your skill...

02:17.528 --> 02:20.270
will be to find those secrets.

02:20.401 --> 02:23.055
They will be your power.

02:23.186 --> 02:24.883
Guard them.

02:25.014 --> 02:27.973
Use them.

02:28.104 --> 02:31.020
Avenge our sex.

02:31.151 --> 02:33.544
Devise strategies

02:33.675 --> 02:37.026
I could not even imagine.

02:37.113 --> 02:38.680
Conquer...

02:38.767 --> 02:41.378
♪ ♪

02:41.509 --> 02:43.163
...or die.

02:43.337 --> 02:46.035
♪ ♪

03:30.122 --> 03:32.908
[Camille breathing heavily]

03:32.995 --> 03:35.780
♪ ♪

03:58.412 --> 03:59.848
[Victoire]
We shouldn't have come here.

03:59.978 --> 04:02.459
We don't belong.

04:02.590 --> 04:04.592
Camille, we have to go.

04:04.766 --> 04:07.769
♪ ♪

04:07.856 --> 04:09.727
She wanted me to stay.

04:09.858 --> 04:11.555
And now she's dead.

04:13.340 --> 04:15.167
"Avenge our sex."

04:16.908 --> 04:19.215
"Conquer theirs."

04:19.346 --> 04:20.869
I will do it.

04:20.999 --> 04:23.611
You cannot be thinking
of Valmont.

04:23.741 --> 04:25.917
It's not about him.

04:26.004 --> 04:29.051
[scoffs] You still love him.

04:29.181 --> 04:31.009
It's not love.

04:31.140 --> 04:32.489
It's war.

04:32.663 --> 04:35.710
♪ ♪

04:35.840 --> 04:38.495
[dramatic string music plays]

04:38.669 --> 04:41.411
♪ ♪

05:50.959 --> 05:54.658
[rumbling, wind howls]

05:59.097 --> 06:00.360
[Camille breathes heavily]

06:00.447 --> 06:03.275
[tense music plays]

06:03.363 --> 06:06.148
♪ ♪

06:09.412 --> 06:11.240
[man] Over there! Take her.

06:13.677 --> 06:15.940
Hey! Up, up, up. Come on.

06:16.071 --> 06:17.725
-[dogs barking]
-There are bad men coming.

06:17.812 --> 06:19.291
You don't know me,
but I'm trying to help you.

06:19.422 --> 06:21.816
Get up.

06:21.946 --> 06:24.775
Please. She's a stranger,
taken a wrong turn.

06:24.862 --> 06:26.864
Jericho will pay
good money for her,

06:26.995 --> 06:29.214
even in that state.

06:33.001 --> 06:35.395
[distant bell tolling,
indistinct chatter]

06:38.180 --> 06:40.182
-[door slams]
-She's gone, sir.

06:40.312 --> 06:42.097
I know she's gone.

06:42.227 --> 06:44.708
Camille seeks to punish me,
but I will find her,

06:44.839 --> 06:46.449
she'll forgive me,
and all will be well.

06:46.536 --> 06:48.146
-[slurps]
-[glass thuds on table]

06:48.233 --> 06:50.671
Now, do you have information?

06:50.758 --> 06:53.238
Did you go to Merteuil?
She must have my letters.

06:53.369 --> 06:55.545
How else would she have been
so brazen with me?

06:55.676 --> 06:58.418
It's her, sir--
Madame de Merteuil.

07:00.550 --> 07:01.595
She's dead.

07:02.813 --> 07:04.859
No. No.

07:04.989 --> 07:07.470
[chuckles]

07:07.601 --> 07:09.211
That is not possible.
I was with her last night.

07:09.341 --> 07:11.474
She was far from dead.

07:11.605 --> 07:13.171
There's been
some error here, Azolan.

07:13.302 --> 07:15.609
I heard it in Les Halles,
first thing.

07:15.739 --> 07:17.959
Yeah, market gossip.

07:18.089 --> 07:19.917
The news came
from the big house.

07:20.048 --> 07:22.833
[somber music plays]

07:23.007 --> 07:25.706
♪ ♪

07:36.891 --> 07:39.415
She was my--

07:39.546 --> 07:40.677
Friend.

07:40.764 --> 07:43.637
♪ ♪

07:43.767 --> 07:45.900
We'll manage.

07:45.987 --> 07:48.250
Have I ever failed to put food
on this table?

07:48.380 --> 07:52.080
I have other friends.
We are not alone.

07:52.254 --> 07:55.039
♪ ♪

08:11.882 --> 08:14.406
[Madame Jericho]
I have a gentleman, Camille.

08:14.494 --> 08:15.799
[liquid pouring]

08:18.889 --> 08:19.890
Camille.

08:21.675 --> 08:24.199
I have a gentleman, Camille.

08:24.329 --> 08:27.681
He's paid for the week.

08:27.811 --> 08:31.598
He wants a girl who's clever
as much as pretty.

08:31.728 --> 08:34.992
Well, isn't that you? Hmm?

08:35.123 --> 08:36.385
The girl
who's always thinking,

08:36.516 --> 08:39.214
always got something to say.

08:39.344 --> 08:42.347
Though never has there been
a word of thanks to me

08:42.478 --> 08:44.524
for sewing you up,

08:44.654 --> 08:47.222
giving you employment.

08:47.309 --> 08:50.921
Now, salt your teeth.

08:51.052 --> 08:53.358
Put rosewater in your hair
and vinegar down below

08:53.489 --> 08:56.579
and make me money.

08:56.710 --> 08:59.451
[dramatic music plays]

08:59.626 --> 09:02.411
♪ ♪

09:19.994 --> 09:22.736
I thought your mistress
was given to embellishment.

09:25.129 --> 09:26.827
I was wrong.

09:26.957 --> 09:30.570
You must have your pick.
What do you want from me?

09:30.700 --> 09:33.355
Or is it possession
that excites you?

09:33.485 --> 09:35.966
I want to know the heart
and mind of women,

09:36.097 --> 09:38.403
to learn what they desire.

09:38.534 --> 09:40.449
[Camille] You believe
we think and act as one.

09:40.580 --> 09:42.712
I desire only freedom.

09:42.843 --> 09:44.496
You should ask
for your money back.

09:44.627 --> 09:48.065
Isn't your work to anticipate
and sate the want of others?

09:49.327 --> 09:51.591
Teach me that.

09:51.721 --> 09:54.594
I want an education
in the female sex...

09:59.076 --> 10:01.426
...so that I might be
its equal.

10:01.557 --> 10:04.255
[romantic harp music plays]

10:04.429 --> 10:05.866
♪ ♪

10:05.996 --> 10:08.042
[Camille] "Your dauphine
yearns for you."

10:09.739 --> 10:13.134
[scoffs]

10:13.221 --> 10:17.529
"You ask me to write to you
with all that I feel,

10:17.660 --> 10:21.055
"but I can only write
one word over and over again.

10:21.185 --> 10:24.667
Valmont, Valmont, Valmont."

10:24.841 --> 10:27.627
♪ ♪

10:34.068 --> 10:36.244
[Pascal] No façade,

10:36.374 --> 10:38.638
no hiding the truth
of what you want.

10:38.725 --> 10:40.596
You haven't paid enough
for the truth.

10:40.727 --> 10:42.467
[chuckles softly]

10:42.598 --> 10:45.122
Isn't the fact that I seek it
payment enough?

10:45.296 --> 10:48.038
♪ ♪

11:03.837 --> 11:06.970
[Camille] "My body is yours.
My heart, too.

11:07.101 --> 11:09.494
"Come to me again.

11:09.625 --> 11:11.627
Claudette."

11:14.151 --> 11:17.067
"You are both lover
and confessor.

11:17.198 --> 11:18.721
"I have talked to you

11:18.852 --> 11:20.984
of things
I would not tell a priest."

11:21.115 --> 11:23.857
[tense music plays]

11:24.031 --> 11:25.946
♪ ♪

11:26.076 --> 11:29.079
Women crave to be known
and understood.

11:30.907 --> 11:33.083
[exhales deeply]

11:33.214 --> 11:36.130
Most men see women
as a surface

11:36.217 --> 11:39.002
in which to reflect themselves.

11:39.176 --> 11:41.701
♪ ♪

11:41.831 --> 11:45.052
[breathing heavily]

11:45.226 --> 11:47.968
♪ ♪

11:49.796 --> 11:51.536
[Pascal grunts]

11:53.190 --> 11:56.019
[breathing heavily]

11:56.193 --> 11:58.892
♪ ♪

12:02.025 --> 12:04.158
"It was an explosion
that night between us

12:04.288 --> 12:06.377
when we both went off
with such a bang."

12:06.508 --> 12:08.162
[Pascal moans]

12:08.292 --> 12:10.817
"How exquisitely
you pulled the trigger.

12:10.947 --> 12:12.601
Your M."

12:12.732 --> 12:14.690
"When we both went
off with such a bang."

12:14.821 --> 12:16.997
[breathing heavily]

12:19.129 --> 12:21.653
"Where are you, pussycat?

12:21.741 --> 12:25.266
"How can it be that both fire
and wetness exist together

12:25.396 --> 12:27.181
"at the same time within me

12:27.311 --> 12:29.270
"without one
extinguishing the other?

12:29.400 --> 12:31.054
Your Florence."

12:31.185 --> 12:32.664
[both breathing heavily]

12:34.623 --> 12:35.842
Oh!

12:36.016 --> 12:38.018
♪ ♪

12:38.105 --> 12:40.107
[both panting]

12:40.237 --> 12:42.631
[Camille moans]

12:42.718 --> 12:45.503
♪ ♪

12:54.991 --> 12:57.167
To hell with you, Valmont.

12:57.341 --> 13:00.040
♪ ♪

13:02.869 --> 13:04.566
[door closes]

13:20.582 --> 13:22.236
[Majordome] Ah, mademoiselle,

13:22.366 --> 13:24.368
you saved me the trouble
of waking you.

13:24.455 --> 13:26.936
There is breakfast waiting--
bread and cheese.

13:28.938 --> 13:30.505
I was thinking
more eggs and ham

13:30.635 --> 13:32.159
and some of the sweet pastries.

13:32.289 --> 13:34.291
In the kitchen, mademoiselle--

13:34.422 --> 13:36.859
the bread and the cheese.

13:36.946 --> 13:40.123
Perhaps you-you didn't hear me.

13:40.254 --> 13:42.778
And when you've quite finished
with the bread and the cheese--

13:42.909 --> 13:45.825
we are a generous house--
there is coffee, too.

13:45.955 --> 13:47.739
I will personally ready
madame's carriage

13:47.870 --> 13:49.611
and see you returned
to wherever it is

13:49.741 --> 13:51.874
you came from with...

13:52.005 --> 13:54.137
whatever you arrived in.

13:54.224 --> 13:56.183
Madame had a wish for me,

13:56.313 --> 13:58.011
a desire
that I should flourish here.

13:58.141 --> 13:59.882
Madame is gone.

14:02.276 --> 14:04.452
I'm the last word
on every matter in this house.

14:07.237 --> 14:09.805
I wonder how her husband
would feel about that.

14:11.676 --> 14:13.591
Is this not his house?

14:13.722 --> 14:16.072
Like kindness,
Monsieur de Merteuil

14:16.203 --> 14:18.205
is a stranger
to Paris these days.

14:18.335 --> 14:20.120
Then I'll wait for him.

14:20.250 --> 14:22.339
I would advise against that.

14:24.689 --> 14:26.735
I don't seek your advice.

14:28.737 --> 14:31.305
Very good, mademoiselle.

14:31.392 --> 14:34.221
[tense music plays]

14:34.308 --> 14:37.050
♪ ♪

14:40.401 --> 14:43.012
Camille made a fool
out of me, too, dear.

14:43.143 --> 14:45.710
You know how much
that little whore owes me?

14:45.797 --> 14:48.322
I'm not the only one who wants
her facedown in a gutter.

14:48.452 --> 14:51.151
But we'll find you
another girl...

14:51.281 --> 14:52.804
a nice girl.

14:55.111 --> 14:58.158
I don't want another girl.
I want Camille.

14:58.288 --> 15:00.856
Perhaps I wasn't clear.
She's gone.

15:00.987 --> 15:03.554
That means
she is no longer here, so--

15:03.685 --> 15:05.556
You misunderstand me.

15:05.687 --> 15:07.602
I wish to buy her...

15:07.732 --> 15:09.909
in installments, of course,

15:09.996 --> 15:13.086
so that when I find her,
she is mine completely.

15:13.216 --> 15:16.393
[dramatic music plays]

15:16.480 --> 15:20.093
What a rarity you are,
paying for what you didn't get.

15:20.180 --> 15:21.529
I'm a man of honor.

15:21.659 --> 15:23.009
Hmm.

15:23.096 --> 15:25.315
♪ ♪

15:25.402 --> 15:27.274
-Which men used to--
-To fuck her?

15:27.404 --> 15:29.058
They all did.

15:29.189 --> 15:31.626
And we're not a house
that takes names.

15:31.800 --> 15:34.237
♪ ♪

15:36.848 --> 15:39.068
You shouldn't waste your money
on Camille, monsieur.

15:39.199 --> 15:40.504
You could pay
all the money in the world,

15:40.635 --> 15:41.810
and she still
wouldn't be yours.

15:41.984 --> 15:44.508
♪ ♪

15:44.595 --> 15:45.727
It was love that made her go...

15:46.946 --> 15:48.599
mad love for Valmont.

15:50.340 --> 15:51.646
Hmm.

15:51.820 --> 15:54.562
♪ ♪

16:00.524 --> 16:03.353
[music intensifies]

16:03.527 --> 16:05.834
♪ ♪

16:20.196 --> 16:22.198
Hello, pussycat.

16:22.329 --> 16:25.158
[Pascal] I have missed you.

16:25.245 --> 16:27.203
-How much?
-Mm.

16:27.334 --> 16:28.422
[Florence chuckles]

16:30.598 --> 16:31.991
[Pascal grunts]

16:32.121 --> 16:34.210
As much as that? [chuckles]

16:34.384 --> 16:37.561
♪ ♪

16:37.692 --> 16:40.782
You have heard Merteuil
is dead?

16:40.869 --> 16:42.958
So sad,

16:43.089 --> 16:45.526
but let's not waste
our precious time.

16:45.656 --> 16:47.963
Let us celebrate the living.

16:49.530 --> 16:51.662
How long do the living have?

16:51.749 --> 16:54.578
Not long enough
to get this off and on again

16:54.665 --> 16:57.625
-before my next engagement.
-Mm.

16:57.755 --> 16:59.583
[gasps]

16:59.714 --> 17:01.281
I think I've proven
my dexterity.

17:01.411 --> 17:04.023
I'll ensure it goes back on
without a crease.

17:04.153 --> 17:05.763
[moans softly]

17:08.679 --> 17:12.074
Let me feel both fire...

17:12.161 --> 17:14.598
and wetness at the same time.

17:14.729 --> 17:16.470
Your words keep me

17:16.557 --> 17:18.515
from the melancholy
I suffer without you..

17:18.646 --> 17:21.040
Poor pussycat.

17:21.170 --> 17:22.563
Hush now.

17:22.737 --> 17:25.305
♪ ♪

17:25.435 --> 17:28.743
-I want to feel that way again.
-Mm.

17:28.873 --> 17:32.616
I read your letters
over and over again.

17:34.488 --> 17:35.793
I must have another.

17:35.880 --> 17:38.144
No more letters.

17:38.231 --> 17:40.624
I've secured
the apartment you wanted...

17:40.755 --> 17:42.713
just for us.

17:42.844 --> 17:45.325
From now on,
anything I wish to tell you,

17:45.455 --> 17:47.892
I shall do so to your face...

17:48.067 --> 17:50.852
♪ ♪

17:55.900 --> 17:59.208
...or another part of you.

17:59.295 --> 18:01.123
My choice.

18:01.297 --> 18:03.821
♪ ♪

18:03.952 --> 18:06.128
[Majordome] I thought
on what you said, mademoiselle,

18:06.259 --> 18:08.174
and as you
so rightly pointed out,

18:08.304 --> 18:10.741
I am not master of this house,

18:10.872 --> 18:14.049
whereas you claim
a unique closeness with Madame.

18:14.136 --> 18:17.748
What has brought about
this change of heart?

18:17.835 --> 18:19.881
The mourners, mademoiselle.

18:20.011 --> 18:22.623
The mourners in need of comfort
for the dear friend--

18:22.710 --> 18:24.451
a loose time in Paris--
they've lost.

18:27.193 --> 18:29.760
It should be you
to offer them that comfort.

18:29.891 --> 18:30.848
[Camille, softly] Oh.

18:32.372 --> 18:34.113
[gasps softly]

18:35.679 --> 18:38.334
[indistinct chatter]

18:40.815 --> 18:42.991
Didn't Madame want you
to flourish?

18:43.078 --> 18:45.907
So flourish.

18:46.037 --> 18:48.736
[chatter continues]

18:52.000 --> 18:54.959
[sighs]
Please don't, Majordome.

18:55.090 --> 18:56.352
[clears throat]

18:56.439 --> 18:58.137
In our grief,
how fortunate we are

18:58.267 --> 19:01.401
to have among us
Madame's closest confidant,

19:01.531 --> 19:03.272
who I'm sure
needs no introduction--

19:03.403 --> 19:06.841
Mademoiselle Camille.

19:06.971 --> 19:08.843
[chatter continues]

19:08.973 --> 19:11.715
[dramatic music plays]

19:11.889 --> 19:14.675
♪ ♪

19:16.938 --> 19:19.984
[chatter continues]

19:20.071 --> 19:22.857
I've never seen her before
in my life.

19:22.944 --> 19:24.293
Her beauty, though.

19:24.424 --> 19:27.601
Perhaps that's why Merteuil
kept her hidden.

19:27.731 --> 19:29.516
-What kept you?
-[Florence chuckles]

19:29.646 --> 19:31.953
Whoever he is,
he should be more discreet.

19:32.083 --> 19:34.695
[chuckles]

19:34.825 --> 19:36.392
Do we know her?

19:36.523 --> 19:39.265
Madame's "closest confidant"
Camille.

19:39.395 --> 19:40.918
[scoffs]

19:41.049 --> 19:42.616
[Majordome] Mourners only.

19:42.746 --> 19:44.400
Perhaps you should go
to your room and pack.

19:44.574 --> 19:47.098
♪ ♪

19:50.101 --> 19:52.930
You acted every night
at Jericho's.

19:53.061 --> 19:54.323
Act now.

19:54.454 --> 19:57.108
[chatter continues]

20:00.982 --> 20:03.463
[chatter stops]

20:03.593 --> 20:06.988
-[Camille] Greetings.
-Mademoiselle.

20:07.118 --> 20:08.381
[woman]
Condolences, mademoiselle.

20:08.511 --> 20:09.773
[man] Good day, mademoiselle.

20:11.775 --> 20:15.910
All alone here with not even
the Marquis for company--

20:16.040 --> 20:18.695
what a waste. [clicks tongue]

20:20.567 --> 20:22.133
[Eloise] Camille is not alone.

20:22.264 --> 20:25.267
We are here.

20:25.398 --> 20:28.183
[Florence] Hmm, but
you must tell us the truth.

20:28.314 --> 20:29.576
[Camille] The truth?

20:29.706 --> 20:31.317
[Eloise]
Well, what really happened?

20:31.447 --> 20:34.102
It can't be so dull
as falling down stairs.

20:34.233 --> 20:36.496
I prefer
not to speak of it, madame.

20:36.583 --> 20:39.150
[Florence]
I never heard her speak of you.

20:39.281 --> 20:41.457
And this great friendship
grew how?

20:41.588 --> 20:45.200
My mother and she were
very close--in the country.

20:45.331 --> 20:46.723
Where in the country?

20:46.854 --> 20:49.248
Carcassonne.

20:49.378 --> 20:51.728
I'm touched at your interest.

20:51.859 --> 20:54.427
It's not interest.

20:54.514 --> 20:57.821
You're a stranger to us,
and our friend is dead,

20:57.952 --> 21:00.607
so you must tell us
every detail

21:00.694 --> 21:02.522
of how you came
from Carcassonne

21:02.652 --> 21:04.306
to Saint-Honoré.

21:04.437 --> 21:06.743
[Camille]
Another time, perhaps.

21:06.874 --> 21:09.006
I'm grieving.

21:09.137 --> 21:11.008
But the Marquise
was my guardian here,

21:11.139 --> 21:15.491
and she would want her friends
to extend the same courtesy.

21:15.622 --> 21:18.451
You'll need
a new guardian, Camille.

21:18.581 --> 21:21.236
Paris is a dangerous place
for the unconnected.

21:21.323 --> 21:23.107
I'm not without connections.

21:23.238 --> 21:25.458
You are unknown. [chuckles]

21:25.545 --> 21:27.851
[plucky music plays]

21:27.982 --> 21:29.288
It's much the same.

21:29.418 --> 21:31.507
[snickers]

21:31.638 --> 21:34.771
Florence, you go too far.

21:34.902 --> 21:36.947
Not far enough.

21:37.034 --> 21:40.211
There's only room for one
fresh-faced pussycat in Paris,

21:40.299 --> 21:42.257
and that's me-ow.

21:42.388 --> 21:45.347
[Eloise giggles]

21:45.434 --> 21:47.784
[Camille] "Adieu, my pussycat.
Your Florence."

21:47.958 --> 21:50.700
♪ ♪

21:57.751 --> 21:59.535
[glass clinks]

21:59.709 --> 22:02.451
♪ ♪

22:04.932 --> 22:08.414
Do fire and wetness still exist
within you at the same time?

22:08.501 --> 22:09.763
I beg your pardon?

22:09.893 --> 22:12.766
Do you wish me to repeat it?

22:12.896 --> 22:16.247
Beware the divine miracle
of Valmont.

22:16.378 --> 22:20.295
Merteuil shared everything
with me.

22:20.426 --> 22:22.428
So come at me,
and I'll come at you harder,

22:22.558 --> 22:24.255
pussycat.

22:24.343 --> 22:26.954
♪ ♪

22:27.084 --> 22:29.870
Is not a friend
of the late Marquise

22:30.000 --> 22:31.785
a friend to us all?

22:31.915 --> 22:33.003
[chuckles]

22:33.090 --> 22:35.789
Welcome to Paris, Camille.

22:35.919 --> 22:38.792
May your stay be a happy one.

22:38.922 --> 22:41.142
[indistinct chatter,
scattered applause]

22:41.229 --> 22:43.666
Thank you.

22:43.753 --> 22:46.539
♪ ♪

22:51.544 --> 22:53.459
See to our guests.

22:53.546 --> 22:56.375
♪ ♪

23:08.343 --> 23:10.954
[both giggling]

23:11.041 --> 23:13.957
♪ ♪

23:14.088 --> 23:16.699
[both] Ahh.

23:16.830 --> 23:19.223
[Victoire chuckles]

23:19.354 --> 23:21.356
You reminded me who I am.

23:21.487 --> 23:23.663
Thank you.

23:23.793 --> 23:25.186
[laughs]

23:25.316 --> 23:27.536
Madame said I had a gift

23:27.667 --> 23:30.539
for finding secrets.

23:30.670 --> 23:33.890
I used one against that woman,

23:33.977 --> 23:36.980
against Florence de Regnier.

23:37.111 --> 23:38.765
But you've never met
her before.

23:38.895 --> 23:40.549
No, but I've read
Valmont's letters,

23:40.680 --> 23:43.204
and they're full
of secrets and confessions.

23:43.334 --> 23:45.598
And now they're mine,

23:45.728 --> 23:49.036
'cause you took them from him
and gave them to me.

23:49.166 --> 23:51.430
Only so you would know
the truth about him.

23:53.606 --> 23:55.608
Now I know the truth
about a lot of people.

23:55.695 --> 23:58.437
[dramatic music plays]

23:58.611 --> 24:01.178
♪ ♪

24:01.265 --> 24:04.312
[Camille chuckles]

24:04.443 --> 24:07.228
[laughter, indistinct chatter]

24:09.273 --> 24:11.885
[Gabriel] Good evening, sir.

24:11.972 --> 24:14.191
I said good evening,
Monsieur Valmont.

24:16.063 --> 24:17.586
Do I know you?

24:17.717 --> 24:19.632
-[Gabriel] By association.
-Whose?

24:19.719 --> 24:21.721
I'll dismiss him
from my circle immediately.

24:21.851 --> 24:24.811
You don't make much
sense to me, monsieur.

24:24.941 --> 24:27.553
How is a man
with no private means

24:27.640 --> 24:29.903
who works as a mapmaker
in the Royal Commission

24:30.033 --> 24:33.733
able to afford evenings
of carriages and good clothes,

24:33.863 --> 24:36.736
not to mention an afternoon
spent with a married comtesse?

24:36.866 --> 24:38.738
If you're one
of my stepmother's spies,

24:38.868 --> 24:41.392
you can tell her the only
interest I require from her

24:41.523 --> 24:42.481
is on the fortune
that I am owed.

24:42.611 --> 24:43.699
I am not.

24:43.830 --> 24:45.309
Then if your question

24:45.440 --> 24:47.790
is simply how do I achieve
my lifestyle,

24:47.877 --> 24:49.313
the answer
is with the natural talents

24:49.444 --> 24:50.750
of charm and good looks.

24:50.880 --> 24:52.969
My sympathies
at your lack of them.

24:53.100 --> 24:54.101
Good night.

24:56.407 --> 24:59.541
[distant indistinct chatter]

24:59.715 --> 25:02.544
♪ ♪

25:02.631 --> 25:04.285
[Azolan] Sir?

25:04.415 --> 25:06.635
A letter for you.

25:06.766 --> 25:10.204
And there's a carriage
waiting downstairs.

25:13.337 --> 25:16.123
[suspenseful music plays]

25:16.297 --> 25:19.039
♪ ♪

25:21.476 --> 25:24.653
With Florence inside...

25:24.784 --> 25:26.394
and with keys
to our new apartment.

25:28.309 --> 25:30.006
We are back, Azolan.

25:30.180 --> 25:32.966
♪ ♪

25:36.360 --> 25:39.494
I had a craving for you...

25:39.625 --> 25:41.322
the very essence of you.

25:41.452 --> 25:44.064
I am flattered.

25:44.194 --> 25:46.545
Take off your shirt, Valmont.

25:46.632 --> 25:49.548
Supper first, perhaps.

25:49.678 --> 25:51.550
Pussycat does not love me.

25:51.680 --> 25:54.727
He won't do what I ask.

25:56.337 --> 25:58.861
[sighs]

25:58.948 --> 26:00.167
[chuckles]

26:02.561 --> 26:05.999
Love is about trust.

26:06.086 --> 26:08.654
We expose ourselves
to one another, do we not?

26:08.784 --> 26:11.091
I am half naked before you.

26:11.221 --> 26:12.396
-[slaps hand]
-Oh.

26:12.527 --> 26:14.355
Take off your britches.

26:14.485 --> 26:16.139
Why don't we first view
the apartment?

26:16.226 --> 26:18.968
If you take it all off.

26:21.362 --> 26:23.190
[gasps]

26:27.281 --> 26:28.761
[giggles]

26:35.419 --> 26:38.422
Florence, my God.
Must I be that vulnerable?

26:38.509 --> 26:40.555
Turn the carriage around.

26:40.642 --> 26:43.645
That was my favorite shirt.

26:43.776 --> 26:46.909
I laid myself so open to you,

26:47.040 --> 26:50.260
such trust...

26:50.391 --> 26:52.828
in wicked Valmont.

26:52.915 --> 26:54.613
What?

26:54.700 --> 26:56.092
You shared my letters
with Merteuil.

26:56.223 --> 26:58.878
My God, no.

26:59.008 --> 27:00.793
But I do believe
she may have taken them

27:00.880 --> 27:02.316
from my possession.

27:02.446 --> 27:05.058
"Beware the divine Valmont"--

27:05.188 --> 27:07.277
that is what she said to me.

27:07.364 --> 27:10.411
-That is what Merteuil said?
-Merteuil told me nothing.

27:10.498 --> 27:12.456
It seems she told
her ward everything.

27:12.587 --> 27:14.284
Merteuil had no ward.

27:14.415 --> 27:17.461
Well, some pretty young thing
would disagree.

27:17.548 --> 27:19.202
What are you talking about?

27:19.333 --> 27:21.552
Who is this woman?

27:21.683 --> 27:22.641
Camille.

27:22.815 --> 27:25.992
♪ ♪

27:26.122 --> 27:30.213
Come near me again
or dare risk my marriage,

27:30.344 --> 27:33.477
and I'll kill you.

27:33.608 --> 27:35.871
-[bangs on carriage wall]
-The girl, too.

27:36.002 --> 27:38.961
-[man] Whoa, there.
-Get out.

27:39.092 --> 27:41.834
I am naked, Florence.

27:41.964 --> 27:44.227
You're vulnerable.

27:44.358 --> 27:47.317
Take this time
to think about what

27:47.404 --> 27:48.667
-you're willing to risk.
-[carriage door opens]

27:51.191 --> 27:54.368
[grunts]

27:54.498 --> 27:55.848
Florence! [knocks on door]

27:55.978 --> 27:57.110
[horse neighs]

27:57.197 --> 27:59.721
♪ ♪

27:59.852 --> 28:02.115
Florence, come back here!

28:02.202 --> 28:04.987
♪ ♪

28:10.036 --> 28:12.168
[dog barks]

28:12.255 --> 28:13.648
-Lovely night, ladies.
-[women gasp]

28:13.779 --> 28:15.694
Though there is a bit
of a chill in the air.

28:15.824 --> 28:17.478
[woman] Oh.
[speaks indistinctly]

28:17.608 --> 28:20.394
[soft music plays]

28:20.524 --> 28:22.396
[knock at door]

28:22.570 --> 28:25.312
♪ ♪

28:28.881 --> 28:30.230
[Camille] Thank you.

28:30.317 --> 28:33.102
♪ ♪

28:47.551 --> 28:49.292
[Pascal clapping hands slowly]

28:49.423 --> 28:51.555
And there I was,

28:51.686 --> 28:54.036
all this time
believing Merteuil

28:54.123 --> 28:56.996
capable of such ingenuity...

28:57.126 --> 28:59.476
when it was you.

28:59.563 --> 29:02.218
Perhaps you have always
underestimated me.

29:05.091 --> 29:07.223
You have something
that belongs to me.

29:07.354 --> 29:08.834
Your dignity?

29:08.921 --> 29:10.096
[Pascal] My letters.

29:12.098 --> 29:13.708
How did you take them?

29:13.839 --> 29:16.929
All that matters
is that they are mine now.

29:17.059 --> 29:20.497
You have no idea what you have
or how to use them.

29:20.628 --> 29:22.325
Yet here I am,
holding every card

29:22.456 --> 29:25.459
and living in Saint-Honoré.

29:25.589 --> 29:28.070
Do you know how dangerous
it is to have them?

29:28.157 --> 29:30.159
Less dangerous
than not having them, I think.

29:30.290 --> 29:31.465
[Pascal]
Oh, Camille, stop this.

29:31.595 --> 29:33.423
You've made your point.

29:33.554 --> 29:34.947
You've punished me.

29:35.077 --> 29:37.253
You've proved
a worthy adversary.

29:39.516 --> 29:40.779
I've learnt my lesson.

29:40.909 --> 29:43.825
I haven't even begun
to teach you.

29:43.956 --> 29:46.045
Do you know what I had to do
to get to the bridge?

29:46.175 --> 29:47.437
To find you'd played
a game with me?

29:47.568 --> 29:49.265
I came to the bridge.

29:49.396 --> 29:50.832
-Liar.
-I came. You were gone.

29:50.963 --> 29:52.225
You came too late.

29:54.618 --> 29:58.231
[chuckles] So you came here...

29:58.361 --> 30:00.755
-to Merteuil?
-I wanted to be with someone

30:00.886 --> 30:02.888
who knew how it felt
to be betrayed.

30:03.018 --> 30:05.455
[Pascal] And you believed that
she would bring you comfort.

30:05.586 --> 30:07.196
I brought her comfort.

30:09.982 --> 30:11.810
And in return,
she has given me all of this.

30:11.897 --> 30:13.507
She has made me safe.

30:13.637 --> 30:16.945
These people are wolves,

30:17.076 --> 30:21.384
and they will enjoy
tearing you apart.

30:21.471 --> 30:23.604
They cannot hurt me
more than you have.

30:23.734 --> 30:26.476
[dramatic music plays]

30:26.650 --> 30:27.956
♪ ♪

30:28.087 --> 30:29.610
[Pascal] Camille.

30:29.740 --> 30:32.352
Camille, I'm sorry.

30:32.482 --> 30:35.311
I'm here now.

30:35.442 --> 30:37.705
Come with me.

30:37.836 --> 30:40.621
[sighing] I told you
if you betrayed me again,

30:40.751 --> 30:43.319
I would not forgive you.

30:43.450 --> 30:45.713
I meant it.

30:45.844 --> 30:47.628
Then I will earn
your forgiveness

30:47.758 --> 30:50.892
if it takes me
the rest of my life.

30:51.066 --> 30:53.895
♪ ♪

30:54.026 --> 30:56.593
Don't make me
call the servant.

30:56.680 --> 30:58.465
I want you gone.

31:00.206 --> 31:01.903
We're a house in mourning.

31:02.077 --> 31:04.863
♪ ♪

31:09.345 --> 31:13.523
[panting]

31:13.610 --> 31:16.396
♪ ♪

31:32.064 --> 31:33.804
[distant clatter]

31:55.783 --> 31:57.393
I miss her, too.

31:59.656 --> 32:03.051
Because of what
she could do for you.

32:03.182 --> 32:05.924
[sighs]
Because she cared for me.

32:08.796 --> 32:11.233
She would never have thrown me
to those people.

32:11.364 --> 32:13.322
Good practice.

32:13.453 --> 32:14.889
There'll be more.

32:18.240 --> 32:21.113
She would have been saddened
you were one of them.

32:26.031 --> 32:28.772
[dramatic music plays]

32:28.947 --> 32:31.732
♪ ♪

32:31.862 --> 32:34.604
[indistinct chatter]

32:34.778 --> 32:37.607
♪ ♪

32:46.399 --> 32:47.966
This way. Carry on.

32:48.140 --> 32:51.143
♪ ♪

32:51.230 --> 32:55.103
[indistinct chatter]

32:55.234 --> 32:57.366
Happy day, mademoiselle.

32:57.497 --> 33:00.369
The Marquis has returned
and requests your presence.

33:17.996 --> 33:19.823
[Jean]
You wear my wife's perfume.

33:26.482 --> 33:29.442
[Camille] It is good
to have you home, sir.

33:29.572 --> 33:33.533
I am sorry it is
in such sad circumstances.

33:33.663 --> 33:35.796
I am sorry that you are sad.

33:37.406 --> 33:39.365
We were very close.

33:39.495 --> 33:41.628
[Jean] From your childhood.

33:41.758 --> 33:43.282
The summers in Carcassonne.

33:43.412 --> 33:45.762
[Camille] Yes, that's right.

33:45.893 --> 33:49.331
And your mother was
my wife's dear friend.

33:52.595 --> 33:54.032
[chuckles]

33:54.162 --> 33:55.685
Forgive me,

33:55.816 --> 33:57.818
but I do hear a lot of stories
in my business.

33:57.948 --> 33:59.515
It's not--

33:59.646 --> 34:01.604
My work takes me a good deal
to Saint-Domingue.

34:01.735 --> 34:03.693
The heat's brutal.

34:03.824 --> 34:06.044
My wife was rarely present.
Do you see my point?

34:06.174 --> 34:08.524
That you were quite separate.

34:08.655 --> 34:10.135
I knew as much.

34:10.222 --> 34:11.788
You knew as much?

34:11.919 --> 34:13.051
You?

34:15.488 --> 34:18.099
My wife could not abide
the heat.

34:18.230 --> 34:20.145
A warm day
would bring her out in hives.

34:20.275 --> 34:22.321
[scoffs]

34:22.451 --> 34:26.064
She has never set foot
south of Paris...

34:26.194 --> 34:28.762
never in Carcassonne.

34:28.849 --> 34:32.070
And no woman of breeding
would ever let me do this.

34:32.200 --> 34:35.247
[tense music plays]

34:35.377 --> 34:38.163
Throw this opportunistic
baggage out.

34:38.337 --> 34:41.079
♪ ♪

34:43.516 --> 34:45.866
Madame was my friend.

34:45.996 --> 34:50.523
She promised to be my guardian,
to guide and protect me.

34:50.653 --> 34:53.265
Then what a tragedy for you
that she fell down the stairs.

34:53.395 --> 34:55.484
You should hurry along.

34:55.615 --> 34:58.400
A woman without a guardian
is at some risk here--

34:58.531 --> 35:00.707
in Paris, I mean.

35:00.837 --> 35:02.143
Get her out.

35:02.317 --> 35:05.059
♪ ♪

35:12.893 --> 35:15.025
Did you give it to him--

35:15.156 --> 35:16.766
the letter she left
for her husband?

35:16.897 --> 35:18.246
There was no letter.

35:18.377 --> 35:21.075
[Camille]
Rather, Majordome, you didn't.

35:22.903 --> 35:24.774
There was no letter.

35:24.905 --> 35:26.820
That letter is a weapon.

35:26.950 --> 35:29.649
Be sure to handle it with care.

35:29.779 --> 35:31.433
Time to pack.

35:37.396 --> 35:38.919
If you cared for her
as you claim to,

35:39.049 --> 35:41.487
you would honor her wishes.

35:41.574 --> 35:43.445
And where you have lost
a friend,

35:43.532 --> 35:44.925
you could have gained
an ally in me.

35:53.977 --> 35:56.850
[sighs] It's over for us here.

35:57.024 --> 35:59.809
♪ ♪

36:06.033 --> 36:07.339
Now we go?

36:09.341 --> 36:11.169
[exhales sharply]

36:13.693 --> 36:16.348
[indistinct chatter]

36:23.006 --> 36:24.007
[Emile] Are you insane?

36:24.138 --> 36:24.965
My God.

36:26.619 --> 36:27.750
Where have you been?

36:27.837 --> 36:29.491
I'm in mourning.

36:29.622 --> 36:31.363
I lost a dear friend.

36:31.493 --> 36:33.321
[scoffs] To mourn,
you would first need a heart.

36:33.452 --> 36:35.410
Stay away from me.
I'm done with you.

36:35.541 --> 36:37.412
Oh, don't be
such a flirt, Emile.

36:37.543 --> 36:40.241
If you want more money, say so.

36:40.372 --> 36:42.896
If you bring me into this,
I'll deny everything.

36:43.026 --> 36:45.377
You had the key, not I.

36:45.507 --> 36:47.553
Do you have a fever?

36:47.683 --> 36:50.251
What are you talking about?

36:50.382 --> 36:52.210
The Commissioner wants you.

36:52.297 --> 36:54.995
[indistinct chatter]

36:58.041 --> 36:59.652
[footsteps approaching]

36:59.782 --> 37:02.220
-[Commissioner] Valmont.
-Sir.

37:02.350 --> 37:04.483
I so rarely have
the pleasure of your time.

37:04.570 --> 37:06.398
How is your wife?

37:06.485 --> 37:08.008
Please, take a seat.

37:11.577 --> 37:14.232
The officer has some questions.

37:14.406 --> 37:17.147
♪ ♪

37:19.541 --> 37:21.282
Sir?

37:21.413 --> 37:24.981
Tell me about the other day,
about the boy thief.

37:25.068 --> 37:29.856
I wasn't at my desk.
You must have all the details.

37:29.986 --> 37:31.771
You seem hostile
to a simple question, monsieur.

37:31.858 --> 37:33.642
Why?

37:33.773 --> 37:35.383
This is a serious matter, no?

37:35.514 --> 37:38.473
Nothing was taken,
nothing of value.

37:38.604 --> 37:40.562
The boy didn't break
into the vault, did he?

37:40.693 --> 37:42.303
He used a key.

37:42.477 --> 37:45.437
♪ ♪

37:45.567 --> 37:47.308
You hold the only one.

37:47.482 --> 37:50.268
♪ ♪

37:51.704 --> 37:53.445
And it is here...

37:53.575 --> 37:54.968
where it's always been.

37:55.055 --> 37:57.840
♪ ♪

37:59.538 --> 38:01.017
Well, then you
must have made a copy.

38:01.148 --> 38:02.715
I had nothing to do with this.

38:02.802 --> 38:05.500
They boy ran into the IÎle,

38:05.631 --> 38:08.155
an area I understand you
are more than familiar with.

38:08.286 --> 38:10.636
Why do you like the IÎle,
monsieur?

38:10.766 --> 38:13.116
It's full of whores
and traitors.

38:13.247 --> 38:14.857
What could it hold
for a gentleman like you?

38:14.988 --> 38:16.946
Officer,
we want no scandal here.

38:17.077 --> 38:18.731
I serve
only to protect the king.

38:18.861 --> 38:20.646
I do not believe this man
to be a danger to the king.

38:22.822 --> 38:25.433
But there is no place here
for a man so...

38:25.564 --> 38:27.348
lacking in morality.

38:27.522 --> 38:30.395
♪ ♪

38:30.482 --> 38:32.353
[chuckles softly]

38:32.527 --> 38:35.269
♪ ♪

38:37.706 --> 38:39.273
[Gabriel] Monsieur.

38:43.886 --> 38:45.453
Perhaps I was worth
a little more respect

38:45.584 --> 38:47.716
than you showed me.

38:47.803 --> 38:50.850
If I've offended your sister
or your mother--

38:50.980 --> 38:53.548
Camille, monsieur...

38:53.635 --> 38:55.245
I'm talking of Camille.

38:55.376 --> 38:58.205
What could you know of her?

38:58.336 --> 39:00.468
-She's mine.
-[Pascal] Yours?

39:00.599 --> 39:03.732
She belongs to no one
but herself and...

39:03.863 --> 39:06.344
never to a man like you.

39:06.474 --> 39:09.564
She ran from me
to be with you.

39:09.695 --> 39:12.654
Yet in all my observations
of you, I do not see her.

39:12.785 --> 39:15.004
I see only your immoral acts
with others,

39:15.135 --> 39:17.050
and now she's gone.

39:17.180 --> 39:20.749
So I will ruin you, monsieur,
for betraying her,

39:20.880 --> 39:23.317
and a man like me
will have her.

39:24.971 --> 39:27.756
♪ ♪

39:31.804 --> 39:33.762
[knock at door]

39:36.156 --> 39:38.071
[Majordome]
You sent for me, sir?

39:38.201 --> 39:39.899
[Jean] How long have you been
with this house?

39:40.029 --> 39:42.205
Twenty years, sir.

39:42.336 --> 39:43.685
[Jean] And in those years,

39:43.772 --> 39:45.339
how many times
have you been in this room,

39:45.470 --> 39:46.819
approximately?

39:46.949 --> 39:48.429
Rarely, sir.

39:48.516 --> 39:50.257
And in my wife's rooms?

39:52.520 --> 39:55.436
Whenever I've been called, sir.

39:55.567 --> 39:58.004
Speaks volumes, does it not?

39:58.134 --> 40:00.223
About the bond between us.

40:01.921 --> 40:04.097
If I have shirked a duty
or been remiss

40:04.227 --> 40:08.318
in any request from you, sir,
I did not know it.

40:08.449 --> 40:10.103
She's dead.

40:12.497 --> 40:14.586
Let's not pretend
you have a place here.

40:20.766 --> 40:23.551
♪ ♪

40:33.692 --> 40:35.476
[door closes]

40:35.650 --> 40:38.436
♪ ♪

40:53.886 --> 40:55.453
A weapon should be
in the hands

40:55.583 --> 40:58.586
of someone who knows
how to use it.

40:58.717 --> 41:01.197
Why didn't you give it
to him?

41:01.328 --> 41:03.286
Because
it would change nothing.

41:03.373 --> 41:05.027
Without this letter,

41:05.158 --> 41:07.465
her death
is simply an accident.

41:07.595 --> 41:11.294
She will have the funeral,
the respect she deserves.

41:17.039 --> 41:18.171
You may read it.

41:27.310 --> 41:31.271
"Jean, my husband...

41:31.401 --> 41:34.492
"my tyrant on his throne,

41:34.622 --> 41:36.319
you are reading the last"...

41:36.406 --> 41:38.713
[Geneviève] ...the last
words I will ever write.

41:38.844 --> 41:41.890
You are reading my confession.

41:42.021 --> 41:44.110
[somber music plays]

41:44.240 --> 41:46.373
I can no longer bear
the secrets

41:46.504 --> 41:49.855
in this sprawling house
and empty marriage.

41:50.029 --> 41:52.118
♪ ♪

41:52.205 --> 41:53.989
I can't read it.
There's a water stain.

41:54.163 --> 41:56.339
♪ ♪

41:56.470 --> 42:00.866
"Apri--the bitter fruit
our marriage bore."

42:00.953 --> 42:02.607
Apricot, perhaps.

42:02.737 --> 42:05.261
They're sweet, not bitter.

42:05.348 --> 42:08.264
I know because I had one once.

42:08.395 --> 42:10.919
"The sour taste
that haunts me

42:11.050 --> 42:13.139
"through this life and the next

42:13.269 --> 42:15.315
is more than I can stomach."

42:17.143 --> 42:19.406
[Geneviève]
You will not mourn me.

42:19.537 --> 42:21.887
Of that, I am sure,

42:22.017 --> 42:24.585
but what has been done here
between us...

42:24.716 --> 42:26.239
[exhaling deeply]

42:26.369 --> 42:28.023
...is at an end.

42:28.197 --> 42:30.939
♪ ♪

42:37.337 --> 42:38.860
What does she mean?

42:38.991 --> 42:40.340
Her marriage.

42:40.470 --> 42:42.168
That is what she
wanted to escape.

42:44.213 --> 42:46.128
I promised her a miracle.

42:46.259 --> 42:47.913
I could not give her that.

42:52.134 --> 42:53.962
But I can protect her now.

42:56.574 --> 42:58.488
Perhaps
I will be your miracle.

43:01.317 --> 43:04.407
You are my enemy's enemy.

43:04.538 --> 43:06.453
That will suffice.

43:16.506 --> 43:19.292
[mysterious music plays]

43:19.466 --> 43:22.077
♪ ♪

43:36.178 --> 43:39.355
[sighs]

43:39.486 --> 43:42.576
[knock at door, door opens]

43:42.707 --> 43:44.622
[door closes]

43:44.796 --> 43:47.537
♪ ♪

43:59.767 --> 44:02.814
Is it the carriage fare
you need?

44:02.944 --> 44:05.120
I think we got off
on the wrong foot, monsieur.

44:05.251 --> 44:07.906
Well... [chuckles]

44:08.036 --> 44:09.777
[Camille]
I fear it might be a mistake,

44:09.908 --> 44:12.388
something you'd regret
if I were to leave.

44:12.519 --> 44:13.781
Oh, don't be a silly girl.

44:13.912 --> 44:15.435
Silly girls always end up
in tears.

44:24.662 --> 44:26.664
Your wife said I had a talent.

44:30.145 --> 44:31.494
Do you know what it is?

44:33.105 --> 44:34.062
I could guess.

44:38.284 --> 44:41.026
I find the things
that people try to hide.

44:43.289 --> 44:45.073
"The secrets
in their sprawling house

44:45.204 --> 44:46.858
"and empty marriage,

44:46.945 --> 44:49.599
"the bitter fruit
our marriage bore,

44:49.687 --> 44:51.427
"the sour taste that haunts me

44:51.558 --> 44:54.430
through this life
and the next."

44:54.561 --> 44:56.258
The madhouse may take
an interest in these ramblings.

44:56.389 --> 44:58.391
I do not.

44:58.521 --> 45:00.262
Your wife's words.

45:02.656 --> 45:04.397
What?

45:04.527 --> 45:06.138
From the letter she left.

45:08.096 --> 45:10.055
She didn't fall.

45:10.185 --> 45:12.492
She took her own life.

45:12.579 --> 45:13.711
No.

45:16.191 --> 45:17.932
Never. She would never.

45:18.063 --> 45:20.326
-It goes against her faith.
-Because of you.

45:25.287 --> 45:28.943
I don't know who you are
or why you're here,

45:29.074 --> 45:31.729
but if you perpetuate this lie,
you will suffer greatly for it.

45:33.731 --> 45:35.994
I have the letter.

45:36.124 --> 45:38.039
Show me.

45:38.170 --> 45:39.780
[chuckles softly]

45:39.911 --> 45:41.739
Then I would be a silly girl.

45:43.958 --> 45:46.613
Support her last wish...

45:46.744 --> 45:49.616
that I flourish here in Paris,

45:49.747 --> 45:52.575
or I will share
your wife's ungodly act

45:52.706 --> 45:54.752
with all your society.

45:56.884 --> 45:58.886
Do you know who I am?

45:59.017 --> 46:00.932
Not a very nice man.

46:04.152 --> 46:05.806
See you at the funeral,
monsieur.

46:10.202 --> 46:12.247
And the Majordome stays.

46:12.378 --> 46:15.163
[dramatic music plays]

46:15.337 --> 46:18.036
♪ ♪

46:24.216 --> 46:27.654
[breathes deeply]

46:27.828 --> 46:30.570
♪ ♪

46:34.356 --> 46:39.057
[indistinct chatter outside]

46:39.187 --> 46:40.841
You need to get ready
for the funeral, sir.

46:40.972 --> 46:42.843
-You're not even shaved.
-I'm busy.

46:42.974 --> 46:44.236
You need to pay
your respects.

46:44.366 --> 46:45.672
No, I need to conserve
my energy.

46:48.196 --> 46:51.460
Colette Tresemme--
recently widowed--

46:51.591 --> 46:53.680
is holding a salon
on Rousseau's Social Contract,

46:53.811 --> 46:55.813
though nobody read that,

46:55.943 --> 46:57.553
and the widow
is too consumed by grief

46:57.684 --> 46:59.860
to see what I might offer.

46:59.991 --> 47:01.601
Sentiment or food.

47:01.731 --> 47:03.646
I can't afford both.

47:03.733 --> 47:06.475
[choir singing solemnly]

47:06.649 --> 47:09.087
♪ ♪

47:09.217 --> 47:11.089
[priest] We are here
to mourn the passing

47:11.219 --> 47:13.961
of the Marquise de Merteuil--

47:14.092 --> 47:18.705
a life dedicated to her
beloved husband, the Marquis.

47:20.011 --> 47:22.100
Through history, the family
has served the royal house,

47:22.230 --> 47:24.493
with the Marquis no exception.

47:24.624 --> 47:26.844
He has shown endurance
and courage

47:26.974 --> 47:28.976
in expanding the range

47:29.107 --> 47:32.110
of our glorious king
and country.

47:32.240 --> 47:35.287
His work in the colonies
overseeing the coffers

47:35.417 --> 47:38.986
the plantations represent
meant long absences,

47:39.117 --> 47:41.859
which the Marquise bore
with grace

47:41.989 --> 47:44.339
and understanding
of their roles--

47:44.470 --> 47:47.038
duty, and honor.

47:48.996 --> 47:52.130
She will be much missed.

47:52.260 --> 47:54.697
[organ music plays,
choir singing in Latin]

47:54.872 --> 47:57.657
♪ ♪

48:00.790 --> 48:05.491
Old Merteuil's funeral seems
to commemorate her husband.

48:05.621 --> 48:08.407
How charming she got a mention
in the end.

48:08.581 --> 48:11.323
♪ ♪

48:23.944 --> 48:26.425
Take comfort, Marquis.

48:26.555 --> 48:28.035
I'm here with you.

48:33.040 --> 48:35.260
She's good. I'll give her that.

48:35.390 --> 48:36.609
But at what?

48:38.045 --> 48:40.830
[choir singing solemnly]

48:40.918 --> 48:43.746
♪ ♪

49:13.863 --> 49:16.301
[Jacqueline] You must put this
agony in God's hands, Marquis.

49:16.431 --> 49:18.825
You must put this agony
in God's hands, Marquis.

49:18.956 --> 49:21.349
You must put this agony
in God's hands, Camille.

49:21.480 --> 49:22.960
I am without the comfort
of your faith,

49:23.047 --> 49:23.786
Madame de Montrachet.

49:23.917 --> 49:27.138
[screams]

49:27.268 --> 49:30.532
[choir resumes singing]

49:30.619 --> 49:33.231
-Camille, what is it?
-I've seen a ghost, Victoire.

49:35.581 --> 49:38.366
♪ ♪

50:00.693 --> 50:04.175
I was overcome.
Must be grief.

50:04.305 --> 50:06.612
I find that unlikely.

50:09.223 --> 50:13.184
The woman you were talking to,
the woman in the veil,

50:13.271 --> 50:15.273
I think perhaps
I knew her once.

50:15.360 --> 50:17.405
From the opera?

50:17.536 --> 50:20.452
You have a box, too?

50:20.582 --> 50:22.149
How could you
possibly know a woman

50:22.280 --> 50:24.586
such as
Jacqueline de Montrachet?

50:27.285 --> 50:30.114
[soft music plays]

50:30.201 --> 50:33.030
♪ ♪

50:35.771 --> 50:38.339
The woman at the funeral...

50:38.470 --> 50:39.732
[breathes deeply]

50:39.862 --> 50:41.908
...she promised me everything.

50:42.082 --> 50:44.258
♪ ♪

50:44.389 --> 50:47.914
She didn't keep her promise...

50:48.045 --> 50:50.482
and she threw me away
as if I were nothing.

50:50.656 --> 50:52.832
♪ ♪

50:52.962 --> 50:54.747
You're scaring me, Camille.

50:54.921 --> 50:57.663
♪ ♪

50:59.143 --> 51:01.406
Don't be scared.

51:01.536 --> 51:03.495
You saved me.

51:03.625 --> 51:05.671
You made me live, for this.

51:05.845 --> 51:07.803
♪ ♪

51:07.890 --> 51:10.067
I'm not nothing.

51:10.241 --> 51:12.243
♪ ♪

51:12.373 --> 51:15.246
And I will make her see that.

51:15.376 --> 51:16.812
And she will suffer.

51:16.899 --> 51:19.685
♪ ♪

51:23.776 --> 51:26.605
[dark music plays]

51:26.692 --> 51:29.477
♪ ♪

51:40.097 --> 51:44.623
[indistinct chatter]

51:44.753 --> 51:46.190
Meet me in the Merteuil box.

51:46.320 --> 51:48.801
What? Where are you going?

51:48.888 --> 51:51.456
C-Camille, I'm not sitting
up there by myself.

51:51.543 --> 51:54.154
I don't even like opera.

51:54.241 --> 51:56.025
I have thought of her every day

51:56.156 --> 51:57.592
these past four years,
Victoire.

51:57.723 --> 51:59.203
I'm tired of waiting.

51:59.333 --> 52:02.075
[dramatic music]

52:02.162 --> 52:05.209
♪ ♪

52:05.296 --> 52:07.167
The Montrachet box.

52:07.341 --> 52:10.127
♪ ♪

52:14.043 --> 52:16.872
[indistinct chatter]

52:16.959 --> 52:19.745
♪ ♪

52:29.668 --> 52:30.625
Ah--

52:38.633 --> 52:41.636
Uh, forgive us, mademoiselle.
[clears throat]

52:41.767 --> 52:43.682
[Camille] Where is
Jacqueline de Montrachet?

52:45.988 --> 52:48.556
Uh, she hasn't been for years.

52:48.687 --> 52:50.689
The box is entirely wasted
on her.

52:52.038 --> 52:53.431
Get out.

52:53.561 --> 52:55.737
Please.

52:55.868 --> 52:57.826
[Chevalier de Saint-Jacque]
Of course. Of course.

52:57.957 --> 53:00.568
[indistinct chatter]

53:03.397 --> 53:06.226
[soft tense music plays]

53:06.400 --> 53:09.142
♪ ♪

53:14.365 --> 53:16.715
[Jacqueline] Put this agony
in God's hands, Camille...

53:16.802 --> 53:19.674
♪ ♪

53:19.805 --> 53:21.459
...or it will destroy you.

53:21.633 --> 53:24.375
♪ ♪

53:27.421 --> 53:30.859
[chuckles]

53:30.990 --> 53:33.384
[scoffs]

53:33.558 --> 53:36.343
♪ ♪

53:39.433 --> 53:42.219
[indistinct chatter]

53:57.625 --> 54:00.280
[Geneviève]
Love is lethal, Camille.

54:00.411 --> 54:02.891
Trust me when I tell you,

54:03.022 --> 54:06.765
your lover
is your future enemy.

54:06.852 --> 54:09.594
[grand orchestral music
playing]

54:09.768 --> 54:12.466
♪ ♪

54:18.342 --> 54:21.040
Avenge our sex.

54:21.170 --> 54:23.738
Devise strategies

54:23.869 --> 54:25.914
I could not even imagine.

54:26.088 --> 54:28.917
♪ ♪

54:37.578 --> 54:38.971
Conquer....

54:39.145 --> 54:41.408
♪ ♪

54:41.495 --> 54:42.975
...or die.

54:43.149 --> 54:45.934
♪ ♪
